WEBVTT

00:00,000 --> 00:02,950
The useful signal in A practical leadership workflow for data and analytics that teams will use 03040530 is how decisions are run when pressure is high.

00:03,000 --> 00:05,950
So the context shifts quickly: content moves fast, but behavior change moves slower. Last week in the weekly operations standup, the blocker was not motivation.

00:06,000 --> 00:08,950
Problem one: volume around practical grows faster than attention and adoption.

00:09,000 --> 00:11,950
Then convert one recurring meeting into a decision checkpoint with explicit next actions.

00:12,000 --> 00:14,950
Then ship in a short sprint so feedback stays close to live work.

00:15,000 --> 00:17,950
Problem two: once roles shift, old support models no longer fit live execution.

00:18,000 --> 00:20,950
So the strategic question is whether the system improves decisions or only produces artifacts.

00:21,000 --> 00:29,950
What do you think?
